The paper proposes a method for adversarial attacks on image and video classification problems, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method involves modifying the border of the image, which could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on state-of-the-art methods, which could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
